Create 'main.ts' with the following content. Replace 'INSERT_ADDRESS' with the SS58 address to query, and replace 'wss://rpc.polkadot.io' with the target chain's WebSocket endpoint if needed.

If the AI fetch tool is blocked, run: curl -sL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/polkadot-developers/polkadot-docs/master/.snippets/code/reference/tools/dedot/client-initialization-via-ws.ts -o main.ts

Then open main.ts and append:
```typescript
const balance = await client.query.system.account('INSERT_ADDRESS');
console.log('Free balance:', balance.data.free);
await client.disconnect();
```

For the full example: the client connects via WsProvider to the node, uses PolkadotApi as the ChainApi interface for type safety, then queries System.Account storage. The PolkadotApi interface type comes from @dedot/chaintypes. If you target a different chain, replace PolkadotApi with the appropriate ChainApi (e.g., KusamaApi) or omit it to fall back to SubstrateApi.

Replace 'bin/polkadart_example.dart' with the following. Substitute 'INSERT_ADDRESS' with the SS58 address to query. The Address.decode() call requires the ss58 package and converts an SS58 address to raw public key bytes used by the query.

```dart
import 'package:polkadart/polkadart.dart';
import 'package:polkadart_example/generated/polkadot/polkadot.dart';
import 'package:ss58/ss58.dart';

void main() async {
  final provider = Provider.fromUri(Uri.parse('wss://rpc.polkadot.io'));
  final polkadot = Polkadot(provider);

  final account = Address.decode('INSERT_ADDRESS');
  final accountInfo = await polkadot.query.system.account(account.pubkey);
  print('Free balance: ${accountInfo.data.free}');

  await provider.disconnect();
}
```

Save the file. To run: dart run

Create a file named 'hardhat.config.ts' with the following content:

```typescript
import { HardhatUserConfig } from 'hardhat/config';
import '@nomicfoundation/hardhat-toolbox';
import 'dotenv/config';

const config: HardhatUserConfig = {
  solidity: {
    version: '0.8.28',
    settings: { evmVersion: 'cancun' }
  },
  networks: {
    polkadotTestnet: {
      url: 'https://services.polkadothub-rpc.com/testnet',
      chainId: 420420417,
      accounts: [process.env.PRIVATE_KEY as string],
      gasPrice: 5000000000000
    }
  },
  ignition: { requiredConfirmations: 1 }
};

export default config;
```

Key points: (1) 'dotenv/config' must be the first functional import. (2) evmVersion: 'cancun' is required for OpenZeppelin v5.4.0+ (mcopy opcode). (3) gasPrice: 5000000000000 (5000 gwei) prevents 'priority is too low' errors on TestNet. (4) requiredConfirmations: 1 prevents Ignition from misreading pending transactions as dropped.

Create 'contracts/MyNFT.sol' with the following OpenZeppelin ERC-721 contract. If the raw file is accessible, fetch it with: curl -sL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/polkadot-developers/polkadot-docs/main/code/smart-contracts/cookbook/smart-contracts/deploy-nft/nft-hardhat/MyNFT.sol -o contracts/MyNFT.sol

Otherwise create it manually:
```solidity
// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
pragma solidity ^0.8.22;

import {ERC721} from '@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol';
import {ERC721URIStorage} from '@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC721/extensions/ERC721URIStorage.sol';
import {Ownable} from '@openzeppelin/contracts/access/Ownable.sol';

contract MyNFT is ERC721, ERC721URIStorage, Ownable {
    uint256 private _nextTokenId;
    constructor(address initialOwner) ERC721('MyNFT', 'MNFT') Ownable(initialOwner) {}
    function safeMint(address to, string memory uri) public onlyOwner {
        uint256 tokenId = _nextTokenId++;
        _safeMint(to, tokenId);
        _setTokenURI(tokenId, uri);
    }
    function tokenURI(uint256 tokenId) public view override(ERC721, ERC721URIStorage) returns (string memory) { return super.tokenURI(tokenId); }
    function supportsInterface(bytes4 interfaceId) public view override(ERC721, ERC721URIStorage) returns (bool) { return super.supportsInterface(interfaceId); }
}
```

